# Payload proxy API route patterns

## Request basics
- Use `defineEventHandler`.
- Read params with `getRouterParam(event, 'id')` etc.
- Read body with `readBody(event)` and default to `{}` on parse errors.

## Authentication
- Use `authenticateWithPayloadCMS(event)` to get `{ token, email }`.
- Decide early whether this is an admin/token request or SSO/email request.
- Only add `Authorization` header when you are intentionally doing an admin/token call.

## Payload base URL resolution
- Prefer `config.payloadBaseUrl || config.public.payloadBaseUrl`.
- In local dev only, you may fallback to `http://localhost:3002`.
- Always `encodeURIComponent` for IDs and query values.

## Safe forwarding
- Set `Content-Type: application/json` when sending JSON.
- For `GET` proxies that return docs with `avatar.url` or media URLs, normalize leading `/` to `payloadBaseUrl + url`.

## Error surfacing
- When `$fetch` throws, capture:
  - `err?.response?.status` → `statusCode`
  - `err?.data` (Payload error body) → `data`
  - `err?.message` → fallback message
- Re-throw with `createError({ statusCode, statusMessage, data })`.

